    • addCookies

      public HttpStepContext addCookies​(URI uri, String header)
      Adds all the defined cookies to cookie jar.
      Parameters:
      uri - the uri these cookies associated with. if null, then cookies are not associated with an URI
      header - is a full header string. It is supposed to be parsed and turned into a list of cookies. RFC 2965 section 3.2.2 set-cookie2 syntax indicates that one header line may contain more than one cookie definitions, so this is a static utility method instead of another constructor.
      Returns:
      self-reference

    • addCookies
